        </div>
        <div class="text">
         <p>
          Thank you for your reply. I hope you know the PT post wasn’t a judgment … Heck, I’m new at this ankle thingy…
         </p>
         <p>
          It’s so great to hear your progress – I AM a couple of months behind you so I look forward to catching up.  I hate that I can’t run around all day… Or that I can’t do a 2 mile walk for exercise on these last remaining sunny Seattle days!!
         </p>
         <p>
          I feel pretty steady and haul my laptop all over creation. Every once in a while I will teeter to the left just a little (I injured my right)… But it seems like a cane would just be another thing to carry… As 90% of the time I feel steady.
          <br />
          I won’t walk down a glassware aisle but I’m sure I’d be fine.
         </p>
         <p>
          It’s crazy, the fear, isn’t it? Who knew the courage it would take to get back to our lives, put on heels, climb stairs… Step up on a curb unassisted…
          <br />
          I will check back on your progress and loop you in on mine when I hit six months!!!!
         </p>
         <p>
          And yes… Square one every time I sit fur a while! Ugh!!!
         </p>
        </div>
        <div class="reply">
